.TH "MONGOC_DATABASE_CREATE_COLLECTION" "3" "2014-08-08" "MongoDB C Driver"
.SH NAME
mongoc_database_create_collection()
.SH "SYNOPSIS"

.nf
.nf
mongoc_collection_t *
mongoc_database_create_collection (mongoc_database_t *database,
                                   const char        *name,
                                   const bson_t      *options,
                                   bson_error_t      *error);
.fi
.fi

.SH "PARAMETERS"

.TP
.B database
A
.BR mongoc_database_t
\&.
.LP
.TP
.B name
The name of the new collection.
.LP
.TP
.B options
An optional bson_t for options to the
.B createDatabase
command.
.LP
.TP
.B error
A location for a
.BR bson_error_t
or
.B NULL
\&.
.LP

.SH "ERRORS"

Errors are propagated via the
.B error
parameter.

.SH "RETURNS"

This function returns a newly allocated
.BR mongoc_collection_t
upon success,
.B NULL
upon failure and
.B error
is set.


